# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment is LAYERED — there is no single template to copy. `make env`
# assembles .env from three sources (later overrides earlier):
#
#   1. config.env          COMMITTED   non-secret config: hosts, URLs, names,
#                                       toggles, tuning. Edit it freely. (this is
#                                       the closest thing to a "template".)
#   2. .env.secrets        GENERATED   auto-minted secrets (mode 600, gitignored).
#                                       Created by `make env` if absent; re-mint
#                                       with `make env-secrets FORCE=1`.
#   3. .env.local          OPTIONAL    external API keys (OAuth/LLM/SMTP) + your
#                                       per-developer overrides (gitignored).
#                                       Template: .env.local.example.
#
# Feature flags are separate: infra/config/cloud/flags.env.cloud (make cloud-up).
# Host ports are separate: scripts/ops/resolve-ports.sh (auto-bumps if busy).
#
# Quick start:
#   make env            # assemble .env (mints .env.secrets on first run)
#   cp .env.local.example .env.local   # only if you need OAuth/LLM/SMTP/etc.
#   make env-check      # mandatory secrets present? enabled features keyed?
#
# Mandatory vs optional:
#   mandatory secrets  -> .env.secrets (always generated)
#   optional secrets   -> .env.local   (blank unless you enable the feature)
#   non-secret config  -> config.env   (committed, has working defaults)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
